{
  "description": {
    "title": "Forward-transmission (lambda) blending of spot and Hotelling prices, and the floor's transmission-immunity",
    "economic_framing": "The K-MSR working paper models a market's capacity to price future scarcity as a forward-transmission coefficient lambda in [0,1]: the delivered allowance price is a convex blend of the static year-by-year spot (competitive) price and the inter-temporal Hotelling price. lambda = 0 is a market that prices no cross-vintage carry (the paper's empirical reading of KAU); lambda = 1 is full Hotelling pricing. Three scenarios run the paper's regimes -- relapse (lambda=0), hold (lambda=0.5), consolidate (lambda=1.0) -- on an identical market with a declining cap (140->110 Mt) and an auction reserve-price floor of 46. The tightening cap makes the spot path steepen (26.7->66.7) while the Hotelling path smooths the same cumulative budget into a gentle 5%/yr ramp (43.3->50.1), so the two components diverge and lambda genuinely moves the delivered price.",
    "citation": "PLANiT, 'Leading Carbon Prices to an Irreversible Industrial Transition' (working paper, July 2026), Sections 3 and 5. Mechanism: pe.features.transmission.solve_transmission_path (modules/transmission/backend/solver.py).",
    "mechanism": "P_delivered(t) = max((1-lambda)*P_comp(t) + lambda*P_hot(t), F_t). Both components are solved with the reserve floor REMOVED; the floor F_t = auction_reserve_price clips the blend LAST (blend-first, clip-last). This order is load-bearing: it makes the floor lambda-independent (enforced at the primary auction, outside the forward channel) while the price ABOVE the floor varies with lambda. P_hot(t) = shadow_price*(1+r)^t with r = discount_rate = 0.05.",
    "participants": "Power E0=100 Mt (max abate 60, slope 2) and Industry E0=60 Mt (max abate 30, slope 4). BAU 160 Mt; carbon_budget = total_cap each year (cumulative 500 Mt drives the Hotelling shadow price).",
    "expected_output": {
      "Static (spot) component price 2026-2029 [USD/tCO2]": [26.66666666666667, 39.99999999999998, 53.33333333333332, 66.66666666666667],
      "Hotelling component price 2026-2029 [USD/tCO2]": [43.3010595703125, 45.46611254882813, 47.73941817626954, 50.12638908508302],
      "Delivered lambda=0.0 (relapse) 2026-2029": [46.0, 46.0, 53.33333333333332, 66.66666666666667],
      "Delivered lambda=0.5 (hold) 2026-2029": [46.0, 46.0, 50.536375754801426, 58.396527875874845],
      "Delivered lambda=1.0 (consolidate) 2026-2029": [46.0, 46.0, 47.73941817626954, 50.12638908508302],
      "hotelling_component_anchor": "The Hotelling component itself rises at the discount rate: 45.46611254882813 / 43.3010595703125 = 1.05 exactly, 50.12638908508302 / 43.3010595703125 = 1.157625 = 1.05^3.",
      "blend_anchor": "lambda=0.5, 2028: (1-0.5)*53.33333 + 0.5*47.73942 = 50.53638, matching the delivered value. lambda endpoints differ where the blend clears above the floor: 2029 delivers 66.667 (lambda=0) vs 50.126 (lambda=1), a 16.5 USD spread.",
      "reading": "Transmission-immunity is visible in 2026-2027: both components sit below the 46 floor, so ALL THREE regimes deliver exactly 46.0 -- the floor is lambda-independent. From 2028 the blend clears above the floor and the delivered price fans out with lambda: the pure-spot path (66.7 by 2029) reflects the raw tightening, while the pure-Hotelling path (50.1) smooths it; lambda=0.5 sits halfway. This is the paper's Result 2 -- a floor that binds is transmission-immune, while the price above it carries the forward signal at strength lambda."
    }
  },
